      "message": "Right - it was the \u0027gDS\u0027 case for desktop. \n\nfwiw:\n\nDEPTH24 STENCIL8 support is required for desktop GL 3.0 and I would be surprised if stencil 8 just isn\u0027t always supported before that too. If we do run into trouble we can re-add the \u0027gDS\u0027 case but require that it always yields 8 stencil bits.\n\nIn ES 2.0, STENCIL_INDEX8 is the only stencil format listed as being stencil-renderable so, I guess, if there is any stenciling available it has to be INDEX8.\n\nIn ES 3.0, the spec flat out states STENCIL_INDEX8 must be supported.",
